<TITLE> Dhaka condemns Gaza war at Rabat meet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh condemned the recent Israeli aggression in Gaza strip on Wednesday, at the 8th Islamic Conference of Information Ministers in Rabat. Information minister Abul Kalam Azad echoed the general feeling of the Moroccan meet, condemning the recent Israeli aggression in Gaza, said a statement of the foreign ministry. He also highlighted the importance of IT and the media sector in the present day world and proposed improvement and cooperation among the Muslim countries in these fields, said the statement. The minister along with many other countries supported a Saudi proposal "to make the role of information in consolidated interfaith dialogue a mandatory item in the agenda of all future conferences of information ministers." Azad left Dhaka for Morocco on Sunday night to attend the four-day conference, that began on Monday. He is expected to return home on Jan 31
